    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="634"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d634">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">417.41/18</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lindsay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your note No. 461 of June 18, 1919,
                    relative to certain British claims against the Government of Nicaragua, notably
                    the so-called “Legation claim”, I have now the honor to advise you of the
                    receipt of a telegram of June 28, 1919, from the American Minister at
                        Managua,<note n="15" xml:id="d634fn15">Not printed.</note> to the effect
                    that the Public Credit Commission accedes to the desire expressed by the
                    Department of State <pb facs="0755" n="670" xml:id="pg_670"/> for the extension
                    until July 30th of the time of acceptance by the British authorities of the
                    offer made in settlement of this claim.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Acting Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
